  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Water and Sanitation Services through the International Medical Corps</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The earthquake damaged much of Port au Prince&#x2019;s already limited water and sanitation infrastructure, increasing health concerns for residents living in crowded camps where disease can travel quickly. The American Red Cross partnered with the International Medical Corps to address these concerns by improving access to safe water, clean latrines and bathing facilities. Additional activities included hygiene promotion, trash collection and drainage projects such as canal clearing. This project reached more than 36,000 people directly in the Port au Prince metropolitan area, with nearly 400,000 indirect beneficiaries.</narrative>
  </description>
